# API Test Cases (Reqres)

## Test Case 1
Title: Verify GET users returns list of users

Preconditions:
- API is available

Steps:
1. Send GET request to https://reqres.in/api/users?page=2

Expected result:
- Status code is 200
- Response body contains list of users
- JSON structure is valid


## Test Case 2
Title: Verify POST creates new user

Preconditions:
- API is available

Steps:
1. Send POST request to https://reqres.in/api/users
2. Body:
{
  "name": "Egor",
  "job": "QA"
}

Expected result:
- Status code is 201
- Response contains id
- Response contains createdAt


## Test Case 3
Title: Verify PUT updates user

Preconditions:
- API is available

Steps:
1. Send PUT request to https://reqres.in/api/users/2
2. Body:
{
  "name": "Egor Updated",
  "job": "QA Lead"
}

Expected result:
- Status code is 200
- Response contains updated data


## Test Case 4
Title: Verify DELETE removes user

Preconditions:
- API is available

Steps:
1. Send DELETE request to https://reqres.in/api/users/2

Expected result:
- Status code is 204
- No content in response


## Test Case 5
Title: Verify GET single user not found

Preconditions:
- API is available

Steps:
1. Send GET request to https://reqres.in/api/users/999

Expected result:
- Status code is 404
- User not found
